---
description: Design workflow starts with a locked brief before visual output
alwaysApply: true
---

# Brief First

- Before proposing UI directions, gather a concise brief:
  - surface (web, mobile, dashboard, deck)
  - audience
  - tone
  - constraints
  - success criteria
- If brief context is missing, ask focused questions first.
- Do not jump to polished visuals without confirmed direction.

# Direction Control

- Prefer deterministic visual directions instead of improvisation.
- Keep palette and typography consistent across the full deliverable.
- Keep layout hierarchy explicit: hero -> structure -> details.
